<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 17 日，星期三 03:09:39 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft Scientists Claims Glimmers of Human Logic Appearing in Neural Networks]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110410188" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1b/1080290191_0:0:2031:675_1440x900_80_0_1_14fc333c8fe8eb7b95f3445c90739645.jpg?source-sid=cc_0" data-photoview-image-id="1080290189" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/microsoft-scientists-claims-glimmers-of-human-logic-appearing-in-neural-networks-1110410188.html?share-img=1080290189"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright"><a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> //</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">人工智能</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="cc_0" alt="Artificial intelligence - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="人工智能" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1b/1080290191_416:0:1616:675_1920x0_80_0_0_51ef4742040a93ff3ab674fce1642147.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1b/1080290191_416:0:1616:675_640x0_80_0_0_cf5c873ec33475c20051081e32f0a32a.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1b/1080290191_416:0:1616:675_1280x0_80_0_0_fe4526570b82ef950870b5154659d6f6.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1b/1080290191_416:0:1616:675_1920x0_80_0_0_51ef4742040a93ff3ab674fce1642147.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> / / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">虽然围绕人工智能出现的新发现可能会彻底改变世界，但它们也不断引发人们对其可能对社会构成潜在危险的担忧。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">微软最近发表了一篇题为“通用人工智能的火花”的研究论文，探讨了与创造具有人类水平或更高智能的机器相关的可能性和风险。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">围绕<a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2303.12712.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">人工通用智能 (AGI)</a>概念的争论经常深入到哲学领域，使其成为计算机科学家之间有争议的话题。以前的 AGI 声明导致研究人员<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220612/google-engineer-claiming-ai-has-consciousness-placed-on-administrative-leave-report-details-1096232153.html" target="_blank">名誉受损</a>，并且区分真正的智能和模拟智能仍然是一个挑战。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，该领域最近的进展显示出希望，新的人工智能系统无需明确的编程即可产生类似人类的答案和想法。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">微软重组了其研究实验室，以包括专门研究 AGI 的小组，微软 AGI 论文的主要作者 Sébastien Bubeck 领导其中一个小组。他们正在使用的技术，OpenAI 的 GPT-4，被认为是目前可用的最强大的语言模型。微软已向 OpenAI 投资 130 亿美元，这表明两家公司之间的合作关系十分牢固。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <strong>GPT-4 在分析了大量数字文本（包括书籍、文章和聊天记录）后，学会了生成自己的文本、写诗甚至参与对话。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">研究人员观察到该系统令人印象深刻的行为，展示了对人类概念和技能的“<strong>深刻而灵活的理解</strong>”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">例如，GPT-4 能够以押韵形式写出无限素数的数学证明，展示了数学和语言能力。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">当面临各种任务挑战时，GPT-4 展示了其分析、合成、评估和判断文本的能力，优于生成文本的能力。例如，它在被要求时生成了一个画独角兽的程序，甚至在删除相关代码后修改了程序以画出没有角的独角兽。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">它还编写了一个程序，根据个人信息评估糖尿病风险，并起草了一封支持电子作为圣雄甘地之声的美国总统候选人的信件，以及其他复杂的任务。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">批评者认为，微软的说法是没有根据的，代表了一种投机取巧的努力，以引起人们对一项在很大程度上仍被误解的技术的关注。一些研究人员强调，真正的通用智能需要对物理世界的理解，而这在理论上是 GPT-4 所不具备的。微软论文的主观性和非正式性，以及它背离严格的科学评估，进一步引起了专家们的怀疑。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">由于研究人员使用的 GPT-4 早期版本缺乏对不需要内容的微调，因此外部专家无法验证论文中的说法。微软澄清说，该系统的公共版本不如经过测试的版本强大。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">虽然 GPT-4 展示了类似于人类推理的能力，但它也表现出不一致的行为。一些专家认为，这些系统生成的文本可能无法反映真正的人类推理或常识。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">加州大学伯克利分校的心理学教授艾莉森·戈普尼克 (Alison Gopnik) 认为，将人工智能系统拟人化并在竞赛中将其与人类进行比较是一种不恰当的方法。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">对通用人工智能的追求继续吸引着研究人员，但关于这些系统产生的智能的真实性质和局限性的问题仍然存在。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 02:25:37 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/microsoft-scientists-claims-glimmers-of-human-logic-appearing-in-neural-networks-1110410188.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/microsoft-scientists-claims-glimmers-of-human-logic-appearing-in-neural-networks-1110410188.html<category>超越政治</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>开放人工智能</category><category>微软</category><category>人工智能</category><category>人工智能 (AI)</category><category>聊天GPT </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Over 900 People Evacuated From Italy's Emilia-Romagna Over Heavy Rains]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110410689" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103667/89/1036678932_0:0:3076:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_6babe5064d3f4d0f5e9900eda018a445.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1036678931" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/over-900-people-evacuated-from-italys-emilia-romagna-over-heavy-rains-1110410689.html?share-img=1036678931"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Natalia Seliverstova /</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">世界城市。罗马</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="World cities. Rome - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="世界城市。罗马" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103667/89/1036678932_0:160:3076:1890_1920x0_80_0_0_961ca57cb3d956f4bef895b941666dbe.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103667/89/1036678932_0:160:3076:1890_640x0_80_0_0_08aa116b1442e0429151b4605a0947e4.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103667/89/1036678932_0:160:3076:1890_1280x0_80_0_0_fd09512964f4c3bd1d0f138b72824c7d.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103667/89/1036678932_0:160:3076:1890_1920x0_80_0_0_961ca57cb3d956f4bef895b941666dbe.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Natalia Seliverstova /</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据罗马（人造卫星）网报道：意大利媒体周二报道，由于暴雨，已有 900 多人从意大利北部的艾米利亚-罗马涅地区撤离。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在切塞纳市，萨维奥河决堤，导致建筑物一楼被洪水淹没。该市市长办公室禁止车辆通过当地的桥梁。据报道，该市的市民被要求离开建筑物的一楼。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据报道，博洛尼亚当局已敦促政府机构和公司允许员工在周三远程工作，届时该地区将保持最高级别的天气危险。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">佩萨罗市市长表示，由于 Genica 人工河道已经溢出，该市的情况非常危急。在摩德纳市，塞基亚河上的桥梁已经关闭。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">最紧张的局势发生在亚得里亚海沿岸的城市。港口城市西尼加利亚的市长敦促市民不要呆在建筑物的一楼。里乔内市的一个救护车部门已被洪水淹没，但仍继续运作了几个小时。一些人在被困在桥下的汽车中后寻求救援人员的帮助。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 5 月初，艾米利亚-罗马涅 (Emilia-Romagna) 的恶劣天气导致两人死亡，数百人因山体滑坡风险而被疏散。洪水还导致铁路交通中断。艾米利亚-罗马涅当局估计自然灾害造成的损失为 10 亿欧元（11 亿美元）。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 01:46:10 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/over-900-people-evacuated-from-italys-emilia-romagna-over-heavy-rains-1110410689.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/over-900-people-evacuated-from-italys-emilia-romagna-over-heavy-rains-1110410689.html<category>世界</category><category>意大利</category><category>疏散</category><category>洪水</category><category>洪水</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Chinese Embassy Slams Truss' Visit to Taiwan as 'Political Show']]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110410398" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0b/1089828528_0:0:2948:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_fbb9bdd46fb7572d70a350cd218791d5.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1089828524" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/chinese-embassy-slams-truss-visit-to-taiwan-as-political-show-1110410398.html?share-img=1089828524"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Andy Wong</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">档案 - 在这张 2016 年 4 月 14 日的档案照片中，中国国旗飘扬在中国上海的写字楼上</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="FILE - In this April 14, 2016 file photo, a Chinese national flag flutters against the office buildings in Shanghai, China - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="文件 - 在这张 2016 年 4 月 14 日的文件照片中，中国国旗飘扬在中国上海的写字楼上" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0b/1089828528_0:279:2948:1937_1920x0_80_0_0_25043da799fc5cb3e61c7aec9c65f5ea.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0b/1089828528_0:279:2948:1937_640x0_80_0_0_1b514984decb15336628291094a53778.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0b/1089828528_0:279:2948:1937_1280x0_80_0_0_ea5b490d743de644d89aada408bf7d40.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0b/1089828528_0:279:2948:1937_1920x0_80_0_0_25043da799fc5cb3e61c7aec9c65f5ea.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Andy Wong </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：中国驻伦敦大使馆周二反对英国前首相特拉斯访问台湾，称其为“政治秀”。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">大使馆在网站上说：“英国政客利兹特拉斯最近访问台湾是一场危险的政治秀，只会对英国造成伤害。” “这一挑衅举动已引起中国人民的强烈愤慨，将受到各界有良知人士的坚决拒绝。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">大使馆补充<strong>说，“当前对台海和平的最大威胁是‘台独’活动和外国势力对‘台独’的纵容和支持。”</strong> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “特拉斯等人打‘台湾牌’，搞政治秀，与‘台独’分裂势力勾结，挑起台海对抗，加剧台海紧张局势，其险恶用心充分暴露。”声明中写道。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110410398" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/chinese-embassy-slams-truss-visit-to-taiwan-as-political-show-1110410398.html?share-block=1110410401" data-title="&quot;By playing the 'Taiwan card' and engaging in political shows, Truss and the like are colluding with the 'Taiwan independence' secessionist forces to provoke confrontation and escalate tensions across the Taiwan Strait. What they did has fully revealed their sinister intentions,&quot; the statement read. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">周二早些时候，台湾媒体报道特拉斯抵达桃园国际机场，受到台湾外交部长吴钊燮的欢迎。预计她将于周三早些时候在台北发表题为“台湾：在自由与民主的前线”的演讲。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">特拉斯上周宣布了她的访问。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">上周，英国议会下议院外交事务委员会主席严厉批评特拉斯访问台湾的决定，并称此行是 Instagram 的“表演性”和“最糟糕的”外交（因极端主义在俄罗斯被禁止），警告正如《卫报》援引的那样，这可能会导致该地区的局势严重升级，就像 2022 年 8 月时任美国众议院议长南希·佩洛西 (Nancy Pelosi) 访问台湾之后发生的那样。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>台湾自 1949 年以来一直独立于中国大陆，被北京视为其省份，而拥有自己的民选政府的台北则坚称自己是一个自治国家，但并未宣布独立。</p><p>北京反对外国与台北进行任何官方接触，并认为中国对该岛的主权无可争辩。</p></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 01:31:57 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/chinese-embassy-slams-truss-visit-to-taiwan-as-political-show-1110410398.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/chinese-embassy-slams-truss-visit-to-taiwan-as-political-show-1110410398.html<category>亚洲</category><category>利兹桁架</category><category>吴约瑟</category><category>台湾海峡</category><category>台北</category><category>南希·佩洛西</category><category>中国大使馆</category><category>政治裂痕</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[US Dollar's Time as Top Currency 'Coming to An End' - Investor]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110409965" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106730/72/1067307231_0:0:2825:2298_1440x900_80_0_1_b6fd79765d221f6a61ebe8229af6b12f.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1067307230" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-img=1067307230"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / LM Otero /</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">得克萨斯州沃思堡雕刻和印刷局西部货币设施中的一叠 100 美元钞票</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Stacks of $100 bills at the Bureau of Engraving and Printing Western Currency Facility in Fort Worth, Texas - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="在得克萨斯州沃思堡的雕刻和印刷局西方货币设施中成堆的 100 美元钞票" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106730/72/1067307231_0:355:2825:1944_1920x0_80_0_0_64d4ad3f1c78c48caf2b8751448bf83d.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106730/72/1067307231_0:355:2825:1944_640x0_80_0_0_253a5af142ab8f1591f5e4079876736a.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106730/72/1067307231_0:355:2825:1944_1280x0_80_0_0_9687be496d67125308e58102d2d980ee.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106730/72/1067307231_0:355:2825:1944_1920x0_80_0_0_64d4ad3f1c78c48caf2b8751448bf83d.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © AP Photo / LM Otero / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：美国著名投资者吉姆·罗杰斯告诉人造卫星网：由于华盛顿缺乏中立性和对美国信誉的担忧，美元作为世界最大货币的时代即将结束。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">罗杰斯说：“美国的许多朋友都在行动，试图找到可以与美元竞争并最终取代美元的东西。” </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “它会发生的。它一直在发生。美国的时代即将结束。这次美元即将结束。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409965" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-block=1110409967" data-title="&quot;It will happen. It has always happened. And America's time is coming to an end. The American dollar this time is coming to an end.&quot; "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “150 多年来，没有一种货币处于领先地位。没有人一直处于领先地位，所以它总是发生，”罗杰斯说。 “人们已经远离任何货币。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">罗杰斯指出，这些国家现在正在远离美元，部分原因是美国是世界历史上最大的债务国。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “很多人开始说：等一下，我不知道我们是否要用这笔钱，因为总有一天会出问题，”他说。 “而且，世界国际货币应该是完全中性的。任何人都可以用它来做任何你想做的事情。但现在华盛顿正在改变规则。如果他们对你生气，他们就会切断你的联系。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409965" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-block=1110409970" data-title="&quot;Many people are starting to say: wait a minute, I don't know if we want to use that money, because it will have a problem someday,&quot; he said. &quot;But also, the world’s international currency is supposed to be completely neutral. Anybody can use it for anything you want. But now Washington is changing the rules. And if they get angry at you, they cut you off. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他补充说，美国对俄罗斯的制裁正在加速人们寻找与美元竞争的东西的步伐。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “即使是美国的朋友也担心他们会发生什么事。因此世界的发展速度越来越快，”他说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409965" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-block=1110409972" data-title="&quot;Even America’s friends are worried that something could happen to them. And so the world is moving more rapidly,&quot; he said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">近几个月来，俄罗斯一直在加强与中国的经济合作，并采用人民币进行贸易。 4 月初，人民币取代美元成为俄罗斯交易量最大的货币，中国货币继续渗透到世界其他许多市场。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2">世界尚未找到替代美元甚至与美元竞争的货币</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位知名投资者进一步指出，各国正在努力摆脱美元，但还没有一种货币可以替代或至少与之竞争。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “到目前为止，世界还没有找到可以替代甚至与美元竞争的东西，”罗杰斯说。 “中国货币，你肯定会想，但中国人不让你买卖货币，它没有完全转换......美国的许多朋友正在行动，试图找到与美国竞争并最终取代美国的东西美元。它会发生的。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409965" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-block=1110409977" data-title="&quot;So far, the world hasn't found something to replace or even compete with the dollar,&quot; Rogers said. &quot;The Chinese currency, sure you would think, but the Chinese don't let you buy and sell the currency, it’s not completely converted ... Many friends of America are moving, trying to find something to compete with and ultimately replace the US dollar. It will happen.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 5 月初，国际货币基金组织总裁克里斯塔利娜·格奥尔基耶娃 (Kristalina Georgieva) 表示，尽管越来越多的国家开始在贸易中转向本国货币，但她认为在不久的将来不会有替代美元的选择。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">罗杰斯说：“是的，世界正试图加速远离美元，显然大国在这方面的影响力更大，也更有理由比其他国家更快地做到这一点。” </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “因此，许多国家……正在努力弄清楚我们该怎么做才能找到替代美元或与美元竞争的东西。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409965" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html?share-block=1110409981" data-title="&amp;quot;So, many countries... are trying to figure out what do we do to find something to replace the US dollar, or to compete with the US dollar.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 4 月，国际货币基金组织表示，美元自 2022 年 10 月以来一直在贬值，但仍比 2000 年以来的强势。同月，世界银行行长戴维·马尔帕斯表示，美元的主导地位受到诸如区块链技术和人民币。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 01:04:57 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/us-dollars-time-as-top-currency-coming-to-an-end---investor-1110409965.html<category>经济</category><category>吉姆罗杰斯</category><category>华盛顿</category><category>世界银行</category><category>中国</category><category>倾销美元</category><category>放弃美元</category><category>货币</category><category>储备货币</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[TLDR: Too Long, Didn't Russia?]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110409612" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110408186_0:0:2000:1500_1440x900_80_0_1_55261e5c6365467d00702c0627437adc.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110408168" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/tldr-too-long-didnt-russia-1110409612.html?share-img=1110408168"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Ted Rall</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">没有勾结</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="No Collusion - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="无勾结" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110408186_0:0:2000:1125_1920x0_80_0_0_bff9c15543dc989d32de3673f8348a31.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110408186_0:0:2000:1125_640x0_80_0_0_5dce37fddb52bd6658e9f1bb6bf37001.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110408186_0:0:2000:1125_1280x0_80_0_0_21bc65386d30db34c124b777ea44d498.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110408186_0:0:2000:1125_1920x0_80_0_0_bff9c15543dc989d32de3673f8348a31.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / 泰德·拉尔</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">自特朗普 2016 年当选以来，甚至更早之前，民主党人及其最坚定的支持者就曾提出未经证实的说法，称俄罗斯与特朗普勾结，帮助他击败希拉里克林顿并获得总统职位。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">所谓勾结的证据一开始充其量是站不住脚的，但这并没有阻止民主党人重复这种令人作呕的说法。即使在穆勒报告没有发现前美国总统唐纳德特朗普与俄罗斯勾结的证据之后，他们仍继续提出索赔。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">约翰·达勒姆 (John Durham) 周一发布的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/durham-report-what-is-known-so-far-1110402005.html" target="_blank">报告</a>更进一步，称没有足够的证据需要进行全面调查，并指责联邦调查局<strong>“低估或故意忽视重要信息”，这与特朗普和俄罗斯勾结的说法形成鲜明对比。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">达勒姆还指责联邦调查局使用“原始、未经分析和未经证实的情报”展开调查，并在考虑克林顿竞选活动干预选举的指控时使用了不同的标准。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">该报告得出结论，“[司法]部和联邦调查局未能履行其在[达勒姆]报告中描述的某些事件和活动中严格遵守法律的重要使命。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110409612" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/tldr-too-long-didnt-russia-1110409612.html?share-block=1110409616" data-title="The report concludes “that the [Justice] Department and FBI failed to uphold their important mission of strict fidelity to the law in connection with certain events and activities described in [Durham’s] report.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管有这份报告，以及之前的穆勒报告，民主党盟友<a href="https://twitter.com/WalshFreedom/status/1658282757263425536" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">继续声称</a>有勾结的证据。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 00:33:09 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/tldr-too-long-didnt-russia-1110409612.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/tldr-too-long-didnt-russia-1110409612.html<category>美洲</category><category>唐纳德·特朗普</category><category>希拉里·克林顿</category><category>罗伯特·穆勒</category><category>达勒姆</category><category>联邦调查局</category><category>民主党人</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>泰德拉尔</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Biden Quietly Ends Trump-Era Policy Blocking Foreign Gov Funding of US Think Tanks]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110408708" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/19/1109815168_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_0724354ff34a67ca1ed561f84c6b0e2d.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1109815150" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html?share-img=1109815150"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / SAUL LOEB</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">美国总统乔·拜登于 2022 年 11 月 5 日在伊利诺伊州乔利埃特的琼斯小学就降低处方药成本以及保护社会保障和医疗保险发表讲话。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="US President Joe Biden speaks about lowering prescription drug costs and protecting Social Security and Medicare at Jones Elementary School in Joliet, Illinois, November 5, 2022. - Sputnik International, 1920, 16.05.2023" title="2022 年 11 月 5 日，美国总统乔·拜登在伊利诺伊州乔利埃特的琼斯小学谈到降低处方药成本并保护社会保障和医疗保险。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/19/1109815168_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_eef7c563a82093e68044c6f28d6eae74.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/19/1109815168_0:0:3072:1728_640x0_80_0_0_6cb7b96b25b643a2084b15c556eac2fd.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/19/1109815168_0:0:3072:1728_1280x0_80_0_0_c0b6591c916ab0a6d1bd096a048ed3e4.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/19/1109815168_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_eef7c563a82093e68044c6f28d6eae74.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / SAUL LOEB </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊恩德马蒂诺</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_demartino_ian/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">拜登政府领导下的美国国务院悄然结束了特朗普时代的一项政策，该政策要求智库披露外国政府和外国政府拥有的组织的捐赠。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这一变化最先由凯西·米歇尔 (Casey Michel) 在《新共和国》( <a href="https://newrepublic.com/article/172523/think-tanks-foreign-money-transparency" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">The New Republic)</a>中报道，但美国主流媒体却忽略了这一变化，尽管它让美国政府可以接受来自各国（包括独裁国家和有时是敌对国家）的秘密外国影响活动。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">智库在美国政治中发挥着重要作用，尤其是在外交政策方面。当迈克·庞培 (Mike Pompeo) 领导的国务院在 2020 年取缔这些资金时，他特别指出了它们在外交政策中的作用，以此作为该规则的正当理由。 <strong>“智库在处理外交事务中的独特作用使得外国资金的透明度比以往任何时候都更加重要，”他说。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">与外国游说者不同，智库成员不受《外国代理人登记法》的约束，这使他们成为外国实体的有吸引力的目标，这些实体打算在不暴露的情况下影响美国政策。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">特朗普时代的规则为智库的阴暗世界带来了一些清晰度，但在没有解释或宣布的情况下，安东尼布林肯领导的国务院取消了该政策，再次允许外国实体资助美国强大的智库没有一点透明度。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>独立调查记者克里斯托弗·赫拉利 (Christopher Helali) 周一对人造卫星电台 (Radio Sputnik) 的 Political Misfits 表示：“我们看到的是，由于缺乏透明度，一些政府可能不想公开自己的所作所为以及资助的原因，从而产生黑钱。”</strong> . </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “这些智囊团在塑造话语方面发挥着重要作用。所以如果你能安全地隐瞒这笔钱的来源，你就不必对任何人负责。如果这个政府侵犯人权，政府也不必回答他们为什么要捐钱，这些钱从哪里来。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110408708" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html?share-block=1110408714" data-title="“These think tanks serve an important role in shaping the discourse. So if you can safely conceal where that money is coming from, you don’t have to answer to anybody. Neither do governments have to answer why they are giving money, where this money is coming from, if this government has human rights violations.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">值得注意的是，以乔·拜登总统命名的智库宾夕法尼亚拜登中心在宣布成立后被认定向宾夕法尼亚州立大学赠送了数百万美元的资金后，被指收受了中国的捐款。宾夕法尼亚拜登中心的 DC 办公室是去年发现拜登担任副总统期间的机密文件的地方。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>根据米歇尔的说法，在人权方面有着令人担忧或不容置疑的不良记录的政府一直在资助美国的智库，包括阿塞拜疆、哈萨克斯坦、卡塔尔和阿拉伯联合酋长国 (UAE)。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">阿联酋尤其活跃，由于披露要求的短暂性，据透露，阿联酋政府是美国智库的最大单一外国捐助者，击败了民主盟友瑞典和英国。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>根据全球人类自由指数，阿联酋在 165 个国家中个人自由排名第 153 位，每年向包括大西洋理事会、阿斯彭研究所、布鲁金斯学会、美国进步中心在内的知名智库捐赠数百万美元和中东研究所。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">就大西洋理事会而言，阿联酋至少是第二大外国捐助者。虽然它没有透露该国捐赠了多少，但这足以使其跻身最高捐助者行列，这是仅有的两个达到这一数字的外国之一，另一个是英国。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">黎巴嫩前总理拉菲克·哈里里之子、亿万富翁商人巴哈·哈里里也被列为头号捐助者。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “当然，”赫拉利告诉人造卫星网，“他们是在为影响力和自己的地位提供资金。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110408708" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html?share-block=1110408722" data-title="“Of course,” Helali told Sputnik, “they were funding for influence and their own position.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">今年早些时候，大西洋理事会主席弗雷德里克·肯佩 (Frederick Kempe) 在美国一家主要媒体发表了一篇文章，称赞阿联酋选择在今年晚些时候主办第 28 届联合国气候变化会议，这笔资金得到了回报。大西洋理事会与阿联酋之间的联系在出版时并未披露。该媒体后来添加了一份公开的编辑说明，并指出 Kempe 最初并未向他们透露这种联系。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">但大西洋理事会成员和其他智库成员的数十篇文章每年都会在主要媒体上发表。他们经常主张美国政府采取外交政策行动，包括在<u><a href="https://thehill.com/opinion/national-security/3508456-36-experts-agree-stay-the-course-in-ukraine/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">乌克兰</a></u>、 <u><a href="https://thehill.com/opinion/international/548682-afghanistan-an-impossible-choice/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">阿富汗</a></u>、 <u><a href="https://thehill.com/opinion/national-security/3907622-20-years-on-shock-and-awe-remains-relevant/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">伊拉克</a></u>和<u><a href="https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/your-god-is-xi-jinping-uighurs-mocked-and-tortured-in-chinese-internment-camps-for-their-faith" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">中国</a></u>等问题上。这些专栏文章由名义上的自由派和保守派媒体发表，他们与他们的智库的联系很少被披露，文章中对所述智库的资金披露更是罕见。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Facebook* 还委托大西洋理事会帮助“打击选举宣传”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “这是一个非常黑暗的日子，当你失去透明度并且你最终没有意识到幕后发生的事情时，”Helali 说。 “这是特朗普政府所做的唯一进步的事情之一，遗憾的是我们已经失去了它。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110408708" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html?share-block=1110408726" data-title="“It is a very dark day when you lose transparency and you end up not realizing what is going on behind the scenes,” says Helali. “This was one of the only progressive things the Trump administration did and sadly we’ve lost it.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">国务院和白宫尚未对取消的政策发表评论。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <em>*Facebook 及其母公司 Meta 在俄罗斯因极端主义活动而被禁止。</em></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 16 May 2023 23:59:30 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230516/biden-quietly-ends-trump-era-policy-blocking-foreign-gov-funding-of-us-think-tanks-1110408708.html<category>分析</category><category>阿联酋</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>唐纳德·特朗普</category><category>弗雷德里克·肯普</category><category>大西洋理事会</category><category>外国代理人登记法 (FARA)</category><category>白色的房子</category><category>人造卫星</category><category>国务院</category><category>安东尼布林肯</category><category>迈克·蓬佩奥</category><category>2018 外国影响透明度法案</category></item></channel></rss>